      • getValue

        public String getValue()
        Description copied from interface: PasswordResetToken
        This is a convenience method to obtain the actual token value required to reset the account's password. For example: 
             PasswordResetToken token = application.sendPasswordResetEmail(emailAddress);
     Account account = application.resetPassword(token.getValue(), "myNewPassword123!")
     //at this point the account's password been successfully modified.
        Specified by:
        getValue in interface PasswordResetToken
        Returns:
        the actual token value required to modify the account's password.
        Since:
        1.0.RC4.6
